  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Clinical, controlled, randomized, prospective study. Ventral hernias between 2(1.5)cm and 7
      cm, laparoscopic surgery with intraperitoneal onlay mesh.

      Three randomization groups of 25 patients giving a total of 75 patients. Mesh is fixated with
      either Protack, Securestrap or Glubran II. Primary outcome: postoperative pain on the 2nd
      postoperative day. Secondary outcomes: pain, quality of life, recurrence and adhesions at 1,
      6, 12, 24, 36, 48 and 60 months postoperative.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
